01:39.808 --> 01:43.270
9:13. Personal note.

01:44.605 --> 01:47.357
When I was a little kid,

01:47.482 --> 01:50.903
my mother told me
not to stare into the sun.

01:50.986 --> 01:54.072
So once, when I was six, I did.

01:54.198 --> 01:58.035
The doctors didn't know
if my eyes would ever heal.

01:59.453 --> 02:01.663
I was terrified,

02:01.788 --> 02:04.291
alone in that darkness.

02:05.501 --> 02:07.503
Slowly,

02:07.628 --> 02:10.881
daylight crept in
through the bandages

02:11.006 --> 02:13.175
and I could see.

02:13.300 --> 02:15.802
But something else
had changed inside me.

02:18.222 --> 02:21.266
That day
I had my first headache.

02:24.436 --> 02:27.523
Jenna, come back here.

02:28.690 --> 02:30.943
Max, Max, can I do it?

02:31.026 --> 02:38.075
- Jenna.
- What's 322 times 491?

02:38.200 --> 02:40.619
158,102. Right?

02:40.744 --> 02:42.746
Right!

02:42.871 --> 02:45.374
OK, 73 divided by 22?

02:45.499 --> 02:48.836
3.318...18...18...

02:48.961 --> 02:52.589
..18...18...18...18...

03:09.064 --> 03:12.401
12:45.
Restate my assumptions.

03:12.568 --> 03:15.237
One: Mathematics
is the language of nature.

03:19.199 --> 03:20.951
Two: Everything around us

03:21.076 --> 03:23.328
can be represented and
understood through numbers.

03:27.374 --> 03:30.919
Three: If you graph the numbers
of any system, patterns emerge.

03:32.880 --> 03:36.967
Therefore, there are patterns
everywhere in nature.

03:39.761 --> 03:41.096
Evidence:

03:41.555 --> 03:43.390
The cycling
of disease epidemics;

03:44.975 --> 03:47.269
the wax and wane
of caribou populations;

03:48.604 --> 03:50.022
sun spot cycles;

03:51.398 --> 03:54.651
the rise and fall of the Nile.

03:58.822 --> 04:01.241
So, what about
the stock market?

04:01.366 --> 04:04.578
The universe of numbers that
represents the global economy.

04:04.703 --> 04:07.748
Millions of hands at work,
billions of minds.

04:07.873 --> 04:11.835
A vast network, screaming
with life. An organism.

04:11.960 --> 04:14.213
A natural organism.

04:14.338 --> 04:16.632
My hypothesis:

04:16.757 --> 04:20.219
Within the stock market,
there is a pattern as well...

04:20.344 --> 04:21.803
Right in front of me,

04:21.928 --> 04:25.432
hiding behind the numbers.
Always has been.

04:25.557 --> 04:27.726
12:50, press return.

04:46.203 --> 04:47.579
Hello.

04:47.704 --> 04:49.164
Maximillian Cohen, please.

04:49.289 --> 04:52.167
- Yeah?
- Hi, it's Marcy Dawson.

04:52.292 --> 04:55.170
I'm a partner at the predictive
strategy firm...

04:55.295 --> 04:57.089
- I told you...
- Sorry I haven't called.

04:57.214 --> 05:00.509
I hoped we could have lunch
tomorrow. Say one o'clock?

05:25.576 --> 05:27.870
- Max, good.
- Hey, Devi.

05:27.995 --> 05:30.581
- I grabbed you some samosas.
- Great.

05:31.540 --> 05:34.001
- Your hair!
- What are you doing?

05:34.126 --> 05:37.045
- You can't go out like that.
- It's fine.

05:37.171 --> 05:40.215
- Don't worry.
- It's fine.

05:41.800 --> 05:44.178
- You need a mom.
- I gotta go.

05:44.970 --> 05:50.100
Max. Here, your samosas.

05:49.885 --> 05:51.887
Thanks.

05:53.722 --> 05:57.184
16:23. Results.

